7Pass is the first KeePass 2.x database (*.kdbx) reader for Windows Phone 7.

Features:
 - Compatible with KeePass 2.x databases protected by a Master password.
 - Supports custom fields, (protected & not protected).
 - Supports urls with embedded fields.
 - Supports group and entry icons (including custom icons).
 - Remembers your password so that you don't have to enter your password every time *.
 - Remembers download URL for frequent update.
 - Has built-in Demo database for trying without affecting trial period.

Support Info:
 - Blog: http://7pass.wordpress.com
 - Source code: https://github.com/7pass/7pass

Version 1.3:
 - Update your DB resets usage count to 1.
 - Added incorrect password prompt.
 - Added support for group/entry icons.
 - Improved notes displaying in entry page.

Version 1.2:
 - Fixed keyboard obscures Open button in Password page.
 - Improved entry page (fields scrolling, larger notes textbox).

Future plan:
 - Add copy & paste support it is available.
 - Add support for entry history.

If you don't have a web server to download your database to your phone, you can use Java Mini Web Server from http://www.jibble.org/miniwebserver/, or any personal web server.

* Please only use this feature when your phone is already locked with a PIN. Doing so without a PIN lock will expose your passwords to anyone getting hold of your phone.

